cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the syntactic monoid of a language, which is a concept from formal language theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the construction of the syntactic monoid as a quotient of a free monoid, which is a topic in algebra and category theory, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) possible sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper characterizes regular languages, which is a topic in automata theory, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible sub-category.
